msgid "Network security"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:6
msgid ""
"Network security is handled on different levels depending on the class of"
" traffic. The different classes are separated by VLANs and protected from"
" Internet traffic by a firewall on the gateway in a Flying Circus "
"location."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:11
msgid "VLAN classes and gateway firewall"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:14
msgid "Frontend network (fe)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:16
msgid ""
"Nodes providing services intended for the general public (users of "
"applications hosted within the Flying Circus) have one or more IPv4/IPv6 "
"addresses in this network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:20
msgid ""
"Traffic to addresses in this network is freely allowed by the gateway "
"firewall."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:23
msgid ""
"Customers should only bind services to this IP address that are intended "
"to be accessed from the internet. Backend services should be bound to the"
" server network."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:28
msgid "Server network (srv)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:30
msgid ""
"All nodes have an address in the server network. This is used by "
"applications for internal communication, e.g. application servers "
"communicating with their database."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:34
msgid ""
"Server networks use a mixture of public and private IP addresses. "
"Outbound traffic is generally possible and will be masqueraded on the "
"gateway firewall if necessary."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:38
msgid ""
"Inbound traffic will be blocked on the gateway firewall with the "
"following exceptions:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:41
msgid "22/tcp (ssh)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:42
msgid "80/tcp (http)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:43
msgid "443/tcp (https)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:44
msgid "5666/tcp (nrpe)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:45
msgid "8140/tcp (puppet)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:47
msgid ""
"Ports 80 and 443 are for backend web services like access statistics and "
"are expected to be turned off in the future."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:51
msgid "Storage network (sto)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:53
msgid ""
"This network is used for SAN traffic (mainly for storage servers to "
"provide the iSCSI volumes to KVM hosts or the backup service). It is only"
" accessible to ring 0 machines owned by the Flying Circus but not "
"customer-owned equipment or virtual machines."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:58
msgid ""
"This network uses private IPv4 addresses that are not routed from the "
"internet. Traffic from outside this network is not allowed."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:62
msgid "Management network (mgm)"
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:64
msgid ""
"This network is used for management purposes only: access to base "
"management controllers (IPMI), switch consoles etc."
msgstr ""

#: ../../src/reference/security/network.rst:67
msgid ""
"It uses private IPv4 addresses that are not routed from the internet. "
"Traffic from outside this network is not allowed."
msgstr ""

